HEADLINE: In Russia, the Mafia Takes Over the Cemeteries 
BYLINE: Judy Woodruff, Steve Harrigan 
HIGHLIGHT: 
In Siberia, cemeteries that had once been reserved for soldiers have been taken 
over by the Russian Mafia. They pay vast sums of money for intricate tombs and 
burials, some costing as much as $75,000. 
